    <h1>LG Dryer Drum Replacement Cost</h1>

    <p>The drum is the central component of your LG dryer, responsible for tumbling and drying your clothes evenly. When the drum becomes damaged, warped, or cracked, it can lead to poor drying performance, unusual noises, and even damage to your clothing. This guide covers the costs, signs, and process of LG dryer drum replacement to help you make an informed decision.</p>

    <h2>Signs Your LG Dryer Drum Needs Replacement</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Visible Cracks or Damage:</strong> Physical damage to the drum interior, including cracks, dents, or rough spots, can snag and tear clothing during the drying cycle.</li>
        <li><strong>Loud Thumping or Scraping Noises:</strong> A warped or misaligned drum produces noticeable thumping sounds as it rotates, indicating structural issues that require attention.</li>
        <li><strong>Clothes Coming Out Damaged:</strong> If your clothes have unexplained tears, snags, or marks after drying, the drum surface may be compromised.</li>
        <li><strong>Drum Not Spinning:</strong> A seized or broken drum shaft prevents rotation entirely, meaning your dryer cannot function at all.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>LG Dryer Drum Replacement Cost Breakdown</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Drum Part Cost:</strong> A genuine LG replacement drum typically costs between $150 and $300, depending on your specific dryer model and drum size.</li>
        <li><strong>Professional Labor Cost:</strong> Due to the complexity of drum replacement, professional installation is recommended. Labor costs typically range from $150 to $250, as the process requires disassembling most of the dryer.</li>
        <li><strong>Additional Components:</strong> During drum replacement, technicians often recommend replacing the drum rollers, belt, and glides simultaneously. These additional parts can add $30 to $80 to the total cost.</li>
        <li><strong>Total Estimated Cost:</strong> Including parts and labor, expect to pay between $300 and $550 for a complete LG dryer drum replacement.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The Drum Replacement Process</h2>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Disconnect Power and Gas:</strong> Safety first. Unplug the dryer and disconnect the gas line if applicable before any work begins.</li>
        <li><strong>Disassemble the Dryer:</strong> The technician removes the top panel, front panel, and bulkhead to access the drum. This requires careful handling of wiring harnesses and door switches.</li>
        <li><strong>Remove the Old Drum:</strong> The drive belt is released from the motor pulley and idler pulley, allowing the drum to be lifted out of the cabinet.</li>
        <li><strong>Install the New Drum:</strong> The replacement drum is positioned in the cabinet, the belt is routed around the drum and pulleys, and all support rollers are aligned.</li>
        <li><strong>Reassemble and Test:</strong> All panels and components are reinstalled, and the dryer is tested through a complete cycle to verify proper operation.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>When to Replace vs. Repair</h2>
    <p>If your LG dryer is less than 8 years old and in otherwise good condition, drum replacement is typically worthwhile. However, if the dryer has multiple failing components or is approaching the end of its expected lifespan (12-15 years), investing in a new dryer may be more cost-effective. Our technicians can help you evaluate the best option for your situation.</p>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>LG dryer drum replacement is a significant repair that restores your dryer to full functionality. While the cost is higher than many other dryer repairs, it is considerably less expensive than purchasing a new appliance. For professional drum replacement service with genuine LG parts, contact us today at (323) 990-7550.</p>

